  "slug": "arroz-caldo-with-tokwa",
  "name": "Arroz Caldo with tokwa",
  "recipe_type": null,
  "brief_description": "Arroz Caldo with tokwa (Chicken Congee with Fried Tofu) is a shared Recipe from Sheryl. she writes: This is my simple Arroz Caldo with tokwa recipe. I prepare this for my family during winter because it helps us feel warm.I like mine spicy, so I put a lot of chili flakes. You can squeeze lemon\u2026",
  "cuisine": "Filipino",
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Wash the white rice."
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Heat the cooking oil."
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Cook the ginger, garlic, and onion for 3 minutes."
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Add the chopped chicken. Cook it until it turns medium brown."
    },
    {
      "position": 5,
      "text": "Add the patis, rice, water, and chicken broth. Wait for it to boil."
    },
    {
      "position": 6,
      "text": "Stir once in a while so that the rice will not stick on the botom of the pan. Cook this for 45 minutes until the consistency of the liquid becomes thick."
    },
    {
      "position": 7,
      "text": "Top with cubed tofu and green onions."
    },
    {
      "position": 8,
      "text": "Season with pepper and additinal fish sauce and chili flakes."
    }
  ],
  "servings": 8,
  "cooking_time_minutes": 45,
